<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-06"><hi rend="italic">June 6,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Friends of American missionaries at Paotingfu are solicitous on account
                            of press reports. Are they adequately protected?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hill</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>